* About the makefile:
----->Changed sscc to gcc
----->Added -fopenmp flag

* There are two parallelization options here:
----->Parallelize the iterations for loop (line 176)
----->Parallelize the tasks for loop (line 183)
*Although the first option is faster, we have selected to parallelize using the second loop

* To run the program with multiple threads, use the argument -t to define number of threads
----->./rgbyuv -i INPUTDIR/rotate_rgbyuv_workloads/libppm/Berlin_Botanischer-Garten_HB_02.ppm -c 10 -t 1
----->./rgbyuv -i INPUTDIR/rotate_rgbyuv_workloads/libppm/Berlin_Botanischer-Garten_HB_02.ppm -c 10 -t 2
----->./rgbyuv -i INPUTDIR/rotate_rgbyuv_workloads/libppm/Berlin_Botanischer-Garten_HB_02.ppm -c 10 -t 4
----->./rgbyuv -i INPUTDIR/rotate_rgbyuv_workloads/libppm/Berlin_Botanischer-Garten_HB_02.ppm -c 10 -t 8
 

